  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" M/s Shri Sendhur Agro & Oil Industries versus Kotak Mahindra Bank Ltd. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_3_714_778','2025INSC328'); ><font size='4'> <strong>M/S SHRI SENDHUR AGRO & OIL INDUSTRIES<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>KOTAK MAHINDRA BANK LTD. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 3 S.C.R. 714</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 328</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003762025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether a complaint filed u/s.138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, can be ordered to be transferred from one court to the other having territorial jurisdiction to try the offence in exercise of powers u/s.406 CrPC on the ground of lack of the court in which the complaint is filed; and whether the expression &ldquo;that for the ends of justice, this Court can transfer any criminal case or appeal to any place&rdquo; in s.406 CrPC embraces in itself the lack of territorial jurisdiction of the court to try the offence u/s.138<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-03-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> TRANSFER PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 608/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_3_714_778','2025INSC328','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></